# Internal working docs + tooling config: committed to the (private) GitHub repo as a living
# backup, but excluded from every Vercel deployment — they are never uploaded, never part of
# the deployment's source snapshot, and never served. The build needs none of them.
# Note: serving was never the risk (only build output + /public are ever served); this file
# exists so these files don't LIVE on Vercel at all.
# 2026-07-24: root cleanup landed — everything internal (handoff docs, copy drafts, scratch,
# scripts) now lives under /_internal/, so one line covers it all.
/_internal/
/.agents
/.claude
/.vscode
# Root-level docs that CANNOT move into /_internal/ (tools read CLAUDE.md and AGENTS.md from the
# repo root; README.md is the conventional landing page; MANAGER.md stays at root by Adinda's call
# 2026-07-24). Each one here is a HAND-MAINTAINED exception — a new root doc must be added by hand.
# Prefer putting new internal files in /_internal/, which is covered automatically forever.
# COMPONENTS.md is queued to move into /_internal/ (scheduled last, see MANAGER.md ACTIVE QUEUE).
CLAUDE.md
AGENTS.md
MANAGER.md
COMPONENTS.md
README.md
skills-lock.json
